            <p>When traveling with any airline, you also need to know the airline's baggage policy. This is a comprehensive guide for passengers to learn about <b>Emirates Airlines' extra baggage</b>, and this blog helps you learn more about baggage terms. Emirates is the leading airline and is known for its excellent services and generous baggage rules. Once you understand the airline's specific baggage allowances, you can see whether you need to purchase extra baggage or not.</p>
            <h2>Standard Baggage Allowance</h2>
            <p>First of all, the two-bag rule is the airline's standard baggage rule on the route, but weight limits are also applicable. Here is the overview.</p>
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> Economy Class:</h3>
            <p>Special Fare: 20 kg</p>
            <p>Saver Fare: 25 kg</p>
            <p>Flex Fare: 30 kg</p>
            <p>Flex Plus Fare: 35 kg</p>
            <p>Premium Economy Class: 35 kg</p>
            <p>Business Class: 40 kg</p>
            <p>First Class: 50 kg</p>
            <p>Your bag weight must not exceed 32 kg.</p>
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> What about the piece concept?</h3>
            <p>It is applied to flights to and from the Americas and Africa. This airline baggage policy specifies the number of pieces allowed and the weight limits per piece.</p>
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> Economy Class:</h3>
            <p>Special Fare: 1 piece up to 23 kg</p>
            <p>Saver, Flex, and Flex Plus Fares: 2 pieces, each up to 23 kg</p>
            <p>Premium Economy Class: 2 pieces, each up to 23 kg</p>
            <p>Business and First Class: 2 pieces, each up to 32 kg</p>
            <p>Each piece's dimensions (length + width + height) must not exceed 158 cm.</p>
            <h2>Purchasing Extra Baggage Allowance</h2>
            <p>People who want to carry more than one-standard allowance can choose the additional baggage. You can select the additional baggage through the official website of Emirates Airlines. Go to the "Manage Your Booking" section and go to the bag purchase. There are two options for choosing the bag: up to 5 kg or a maximum of 50 kg. The baggage fee for the online Emirates is 50% less than the airport baggage fee. At the airport, you can add or pay the extra baggage fee at check-in; fees, perfumes, and routes are charged.</p>
            <h2>Special Allowances for Emirates Skywards Members</h2>
            <p>People who are members of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/emirates-airlines.aspx"><b>Emirates Airlines</b></a> ' frequent flyer program, Emirates Skywards, can also enjoy the additional baggage services based on their membership tier.</p>
            <p>Silver Members: An additional 12 kg</p>
